                     <p>
                        <placeName>Oxford, St. Aldate’s</placeName>
                        <!--insert summary text from Wigram if necessary.-->

<persName><forename>Richard</forename> of  <surname>Wodehay</surname></persName>, mayor of Oxford, inspects, at the request of <persName><forename>Robert</forename> son of  <surname>Walter</surname></persName> Portreve of Brehull [Brill], an enrollment of the following writing read in the Hustings at Oxford on Monday, the feast of S. Hillary, 38 Ed. III: <persName><forename>Richard</forename> of  <surname>Wodehay</surname></persName>, <persName><forename>Hugh</forename> de  <surname>Saundresdone</surname></persName>, rector St <persName><forename>Peter</forename> le  <surname>Bailey</surname></persName>’s, <persName><forename>Adam</forename> of  <surname>Plumpton</surname> , clerk</persName>, <persName><forename>Walter</forename> of  <surname>Baldyndone</surname></persName>, rector of the church of Upledecombe, <persName><forename>John</forename> of  <surname>Hertwell</surname></persName>, and <persName><forename>Walter</forename> of  <surname>Clyne</surname></persName> of Oxford, grant to R. f. W. P. of Brehull, 40/- rent from the tenements late of <persName><forename>John</forename> of  <surname>St</surname></persName>. F., viz. 4 messuages, 7 shops, and 7½ acres of meadow. [For the positions of these see the <hi rend="italic">Cartulary,</hi> no. 314.] Witnesses: <persName><forename>William</forename> of  <surname>Godesale</surname></persName> and <persName><forename>Geoffrey</forename> of  <surname>Lodewelle</surname></persName>, bailiffs, <persName><forename>Walter</forename> of  <surname>Clyne</surname></persName>, [<gap/>] of Benham, John of N[or]tone, John G[ib]b[es], <persName><forename>John</forename> of  <surname>Northampton</surname></persName>. Given at Oxford. <origDate>
                           <supplied>Jan. 13, 1365.</supplied>
                        </origDate> 
                        <origDate>1 Jan. 38 Ed. III.</origDate>
                     </p>
